<i>noun</i>: 희열 [히열], 환희 [환히], 환락 [활락], 쾌락 [쾌락], 신 [신], 반가움 [반가움], 낙 [낙] <br>
<ul>
<li><i>noun</i><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>희열 [히열]</dt><br>
<dd>delight; joy; happiness</dd><br>
<dd>기쁨과 즐거움. 또는 기뻐하고 즐거워함.</dd><br>
<dd>Happiness and delight; or an act of being happy and delighted.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>환희 [환히]</dt><br>
<dd>delight; joy; happiness</dd><br>
<dd>크게 기뻐함. 또는 큰 기쁨.</dd><br>
<dd>A state of being extremely happy; or a feeling of great joy.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>환락 [활락]</dt><br>
<dd>pleasure; amusement; delight</dd><br>
<dd>매우 기뻐하고 즐거워함. 또는 매우 기쁘고 즐거운 것.</dd><br>
<dd>A state of being extremely happy and delightful; or a source of such a happiness and delight.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>쾌락 [쾌락]</dt><br>
<dd>pleasure; delight</dd><br>
<dd>유쾌하고 즐거움. 또는 그런 느낌.</dd><br>
<dd>The state of feeling pleasant and happy, or such a feeling.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>신 [신]</dt><br>
<dd>joy; delight</dd><br>
<dd>흥이 나고 즐거운 기분.</dd><br>
<dd>A feeling of being excited and joyful.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>반가움 [반가움]</dt><br>
<dd>delight; joy; gladness</dd><br>
<dd>보고 싶은 사람을 만나서 즐겁고 기쁜 감정이나 마음.</dd><br>
<dd>Joyful and happy feelings from meeting a person that one missed.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>낙 [낙]</dt><br>
<dd>joy; pleasure; delight</dd><br>
<dd>살아가면서 느끼는 즐거움이나 재미.</dd><br>
<dd>Happiness or fun one feels in his/her life.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>